{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Standardised aftercare information and follow-up after endometriosis surgery",
        "additional_details": "Patients are often discharged without clear guidance & wait months for a follow up, regardless of surgical severity.\r\n\r\nConversely, the NHS routinely provides discharge information for many other conditions.\r\n\r\nWe call on Government to ensure the NHS provides standardised, severity-based post-operative information following endometriosis surgery, including recovery timelines, work/activity guidance, red-flag symptoms etc, thus improving patient safety, recovery outcomes & consistency of care.",
        "background": "We want the Government to ensure national mandatory, standardised post-operative aftercare guidance for patients undergoing endometriosis surgery, with information tailored to the severity and extent of surgery.",
